> Crispy breadcrumbs are a low-effort way to add tons of flavor and texture to your meal. This tasty topping perfectly accentuates tender, cheese-stuffed tortelloni. The pillowy pasta is coated in rich garlic-herb butter and tossed with sweet sautéed shallot and roasted veggies for bite after bite deliciousness. Can you say pasta night bliss?

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise), cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve @roma tomatoes{2}(halved, cut into ½-inch-thick wedges). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Toss zucchini and tomatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just softened, ~{10%seconds}. Stir in garlic, @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and @chili flakes{pinch}.

Melt @plain butter{1/2%tbsp} in a #small pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until golden and toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper. Once water is boiling, add @cheese tortelloni{9%oz} to #pot{}. Cook until al dente, ~{3-4%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in pot used for tortelloni over medium-high heat. Add shallot; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add garlic herb butter; cook until melted, ~{30-60%seconds}. Stir in ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water. Add cooked tortelloni; stir to coat. If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until tortelloni is thoroughly coated in sauce. Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper.

Divide tortelloni between #bowls{}. Top with roasted veggies. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, toasted panko to taste, and a pinch of remaining chili flakes if desired.